{
  "texts": [
    "These baselines represent a range of approaches, with MOSA-Net using features extracted from pretrained SSL models and other sources, SSL-MOS conducting finetuning of SSL models, and LDNet conducting listener-dependent modeling.",
    "Team approachesIn the following, we reference and briefly summarize papers released by participants, which either described their submitted system or provided an analysis.• The UTMOS (University of Tokyo MOS) system (T17) [134] was one of the best-performing systems, scoring the highest on several metrics.",
    "It ensembles strong and weak learners.",
    "The strong learners were modified SSL-MOS systems with additional techniques, including contrastive learning, listener-dependent modeling, and phoneme encodings.",
    "The weak learners were regression models including linear regression, decision tree, and kernel methods."
  ]
}